The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, September 07, 2004 

 BRIEFS

 Farakka, Sept. 6: Union water resources minister Priya Ranjan Das Munshi said he is planning to allocate more funds to combat erosion after a meeting with MPs, MLAs and sabhadhipatis of Malda and Murshidabad. 

 He promised to request the Prime Minister to include erosion in the list of national calamities and said a technical team has been told to submit a report on the condition of the Farakka barrage.

 Calcutta: The city and several districts experienced blackouts as two Kolaghat units collapsed and the National Thermal Power Corporation generated less at Farakka and Talcher. The combined shortfall in the CESC and electricity board areas was early 500 mw in the evening. 

 Durgapur: Postmaster of Amlajora rural post-office Tarapada Singha has been suspended for defalcation of funds to the tune of Rs 2 lakh. He was found guilty after an inquiry following allegations by account holders at Amlajora, 160 km from Calcutta.

 Kalyani: The subdivisional officer filed an FIR against the towns only cable TV operator and sealed its office for evading amusement tax worth Rs 7 lakh.

 Bolpur: President A.P.J. Abdul Kalam is likely to visit Visva-Bharati on October 1. He is the universitys visitor (paridarshak).




